frus:attachment.p:
Sunday morning word came to him that Cho Shoa Syon, governor’s
                                overseer of the palace building, had seized 26 of the best pieces;
                                that when he was taking it a Japanese boy had asked why he was
                                taking it since it had been bought for a foreigner by Syen On Chun;
                                and that he replied, “This is the people’s lumber and we want it for
                                the palace.”
